OL,3,CCalls for Guernsey to introduce a
OL,4,Cpublic sex offenders register
OL,6,FMandy, whose name we have changed to
OL,7,Fprotect her identity, was raped when
OL,8,Fshe was a teenager and is one of those
OL,9,Fcalling for the register.
OL,11,FShe says: "I see them and I walk the
OL,12,Fother way because I don't want to walk
OL,13,Fpast them. Even if it happened thirty
OL,14,Fyears ago they should be on a register
OL,15,Fand it should be public. We need to
OL,16,Fknow who they are.
OL,18,FThe lack of Guernsey's public register
OL,19,Fhas led to some taking matters into
OL,20,Ftheir own hands.
