OL,3,CCalls for Guernsey to introduce a
OL,4,Cpublic sex offenders register
OL,6,FWhat these victims in Guernsey are
OL,7,Fcalling for is a fully public register
OL,8,F- for anyone convicted of any sexual
OL,9,Foffence.
OL,11,FVictims we spoke to say it would
OL,12,Fprovide peace of mind, avoid social
OL,13,Fmedia lists populated by rumour, and
OL,14,Fcreate a powerful deterrent.
OL,16,FHowever, there are concerns a public
OL,17,Fregister would increase vigilantism
OL,18,Fand essentially cut people out of
OL,19,Fsociety or push criminal problems to
OL,20,Fother jurisdictions.
